          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "/BY AUTHORS/.THE CALCULATED EXCITATION FUNCTIONS FOR",
                "FM-250 GIVE THE SAME SHAPES AS THE EXPERIMENTAL ONES",
                "SHOWING THAT THE FE-250 ISOTOPE IS PRODUCED VIA THE",
                "COMPOUND NUCLEUS REACTIONS,PU-242(C-12,4N)FE-250 OR",
                "U-238(O-16,4N)FM-250.",
                "/BY AUTHORS/.THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN THE EXCITATION",
                "FUNCTIONS FOR FM-250 AND CF-244-246 PRODUCED IN THE",
                "C-12+PU-242 AND THE O-16+U-238 REACTIONS APPEARS TO",
                "BE EXPLAINED BY THE DIFFERENCE IN THE COULOMB-BARRIER",
                "ENERGIES FOR THE TWO SYSTEMS.THE FERMIUM ISOTOPE IS",
                "PRODUCED BY NEUTRON EVAPORATION FOLLOWING A FUSION",
                "REACTION,WHILE THE CALIFORNIUM ISOTOPE ARE FORMED BY",
                "TRANSFERS OF C FRAGMENTS FOR O-U SYSTEM AND BE FRAG-",
                "MENTS FOR C+PU SYSTEM.IT IS FOUND THAT THE ISOTOPE OF",
                "CM-242-244 ARE ALSO PRODUCED IN THE C-12+PU-242 REAC-",
                "TION AND CM-242 IN THE O-16+U-238 REACTION.THESE ISO-",
                "TOPES ARE FORMED BY TRANSFER OF BE AND HE FRAGMENTS",
                "FROM PROJECTILE TO TARGET."
              ]
            }
          ],
